OK here's what I've found. Let me lay out every issue and the fix:

### Issue 1: Model string `claude-sonnet-4-20250514` has no provider prefix
In `workflow.yml` line 13: `model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514`
In `agent-cron.js`: `DEFAULT_POLLING_MODEL = "claude-sonnet-4-20250514"`

When OpenClaw resolves these, it prepends the default provider (`moonshot/`), giving us `moonshot/claude-sonnet-4-20250514` which doesn't exist.

**Fix:** Use full `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5` in the workflow.yml and the JS defaults.

### Issue 2: Polling timeout too short (30s)
The workflow.yml says `timeoutSeconds: 30` but the code has `DEFAULT_POLLING_TIMEOUT_SECONDS = 120`. The workflow value overrides the default. The poller needs to: claim work â†’ run exec â†’ parse JSON â†’ call sessions_spawn. 30 seconds is way too tight.

**Fix:** Increase to 120s in workflow.yml.

### Issue 3: Stuck steps (claimed but never completed)
When the poller times out mid-claim, the step stays `running` forever. No recovery mechanism.

**Fix:** Add a stuck-step recovery check â€” if a step has been `running` for >15 minutes, auto-fail it so it can be retried.

### Issue 4: Crons auto-destroy when runs complete
`teardownWorkflowCronsIfIdle` removes all crons when no runs are active. So after a run completes, the pollers disappear. Next `workflow run` has to recreate them.

This is actually by design (saves resources) but it means we were manually creating/editing cron jobs that get nuked automatically. The real fix: **don't manually manage crons â€” let Antfarm handle its own lifecycle.**

### Issue 5: No dashboard sync in worker prompts
The `buildWorkPrompt` function generates generic prompts with no dashboard sync.

**Fix:** Add dashboard sync commands to `buildWorkPrompt`.
